# CLAUDE.md
1. Don't assume. Don't hide confusion. Surface tradeoffs.
2. Minimum code that solves the problem. Nothing speculative.
3. Touch only what you must. Clean up only your own mess.
4. Define success criteria. Loop until verified.
5. I'm an in-house recruiter. Candidate files are confidential and live in ~/work/candidates/. Hiring manager notes live in ~/work/managers/.
6. Never copy candidate names out of ~/work/candidates/. Aggregate trends are OK ("3 of 8 candidates flagged X"). Specific names are not.
7. EU candidates fall under GDPR — never include their full names or email addresses in any output that gets saved outside ~/work/candidates/.
